      "sha256": "1c24f9fc8f44f74fd767fdd8e66a45782623f048e4588eed0234a06e3175ee0c",
      "source_region": "div.problem-additional-text",
      "text": "A problem of Erd\\H{o}s, Hajnal, and Rado."
    },
    "statement": {
      "sha256": "b6c4028c8579021e40414d876a878725431970a6eb2659bc3b58e03f8e8238fc",
      "source_region": "div#content",
      "text": "Let $r\\geq 2$ be finite and $\\lambda$ be an infinite cardinal. Let $\\kappa_\\alpha$ be cardinals for all $\\alpha<\\gamma$. \n\nIs it true that\\[2^\\lambda \\to (\\kappa_\\alpha+1)_{\\alpha<\\gamma}^{r+1}\\]implies\\[\\lambda \\to (\\kappa_\\alpha)_{\\alpha<\\gamma}^{r}?\\]Here $+$ means cardinal addition, so that $\\kappa_\\alpha+1=\\kappa_\\alpha$ if $\\kappa_\\alpha$ is infinite."
    }
  },
